          We flagged Sánchez as the LHH wildcard before the game with no Sugano history and a .312 prior. He went 1-for-2 with a single, posting a .444 actual wOBA. More importantly, Sugano went to his Split-Finger against the lefty exactly as projected, and Sánchez put one in play. The LHH angle we identified in the preview held up.
